  "texts": [
    "To compute AI-induced bias in participants, we subtracted the participant's bias in the baseline block from the bias in the interaction blocks.",
    "AI-induced bias = Bias AI interaction blocks -Bias baseline At the group level, no systematic bias in baseline responses was detected (mean response at baseline = 0.62; permutation test against 0: P = 0.28; d = 0.1; 95% CI = -0.48 to 1.76).",
    "To define accuracy, we first computed an error score for each participant:",
    "Then, this quantity was subtracted from the error score in the baseline block, indicating changes in accuracy.",
    "That is, if errors when interacting with the AI (second quantity) were smaller than baseline errors (first quantity), the change would be positive, indicating that participants became more accurate."
  ],
